    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Camillo Ghilino to Miklós Oláh (Milan, 1534)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">Christina, Duchess of Milan, is in the countryside. If
                            the Queen and Dorothea, Electress Palatine, are not receiving any
                            letters from her, it is because the bearer of the letter was in a
                            hury.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Idem Nicolao Olao salutem.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.2"><persName>Dux mea illustrissima</persName><note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.1">Christina of Denmark, Duchess of Milan.</note>
                        rusticatur.<note type="critic" xml:id="note.2">“Hunting-parties were held
                        for Christina’s amusement both in Vigevano and in Count Massimiliano’s woods
                        in Cussago.” <hi rend="smallcap">Cartwright</hi> 1913, 99.</note> Quare si
                    serenissima <persName>regina</persName> et excellentissima domina
                        <persName>Dorothea</persName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.3">Dorothea of
                        Denmark and Norway (1520–1580), Electress Palatine was Christina of
                        Denmark’s sister.</note> litteras ab ea non habebunt, in causa est, quod
                    tabellarius valde festinabat. Vale et te salvum cupio.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.3"><placeName>Mediolano</placeName> 1534.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
